[thinking] **Evaluating Git test setup**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m considering how GitExe depends on the external git CLI. I wonder if this setup goes beyond a normal generated test scaffold. With Git installed on Ubuntu and no driver setup, it seems generated tests should assume the git executable is available, creating a temporary local repository for testing. Also, I’m thinking about including environment variables and system properties in agent guidance. If tests require Git operations, they must create a local repository, though the existing tests have already achieved some coverage.
